<HEADLINE> Lithuania Bids to Join NATO Despite Russia's Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania wants to join NATO in
spite of Russia's opposition and hopes Hungary will support its
membership bid, visiting Lithuanian Defense Minister Cheslovas
Stankevichus said here today.
</P>
<P>
The minister was speaking at a joint press conference with
Hungarian Defense Minister Gyorgy Keleti following talks.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, in Moscow, Viktor Afanasyevsky, Russia's
deputy foreign minister said the admission of the three Baltic
countries -- Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania -- into NATO was not in
the interests of their security and would cause tension in the
region. 
