<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, June 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA -- Canadian voters head to polls today to decide who
will lead them into the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
ALGIERS -- A home-made bomb exploded in the capital of Algiers
on Monday morning, killing seven people and wounding another 37.
</P>
<P>
The explosion followed two bomb attacks on Sunday afternoon in
which eight people were killed and 40 others injured.
</P>
<P>
HARARE -- The 33rd ordinary conference of heads of state and
government of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) opened here
Monday with the topic of maintenance of peace and economic
development stressed.
</P>
<P>
FREETOWN -- Intense fighting is still going on Monday in Sierra
Leone's capital Freetown between Nigeria-led west African
intervening troops and the coup soldiers allied with rebels.
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French President Jacques Chirac Monday nominated the
Socialist Party leader Lionel Jospin as the new prime minister of
France, formally starting his cohabitation with his ideological
opponents. 
</P>
