<HEADLINE> Iran Blanks Maldives in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian nationals launched
their scoring spree by crushing the Maldives 17-0 here on Monday
at the World Cup Asian zone Group 2 qualifier.
</P>
<P>
The group two opener was developed into a lop-sided conflict
with the Iranian footers enjoying upperhands everywhere in the
pitch.
</P>
<P>
By exploiting their height advantages, the Iranian eleven
scored six goals in a row before the half break and did not
hesitate to enlarge their account until the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
Bagheri Koroygh Karim alone slammed home six goals for the
winner, who was tipped to advance to the second round of the Asian
qualifying tournament.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the game, Iranian officials said they came over here
to accumulate enough goals and points in order to battle for the
tickets to the 1998 World Cup finals in France.
</P>
<P>
Kirghizstan failed to make the trip due to flight problems and
its scheduled game against Syria had been postponed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
