<HEADLINE> Belarus PM Meets Chinese Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Belarus Prime Minister Sergei
Stepanovich Ling held talks with visiting Chinese Defense Minister
Chi Haotian in Minsk today on furthering bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Ling expressed his satisfaction at the development of friendly
cooperation between the two countries and said that Belarus-China
relations have a bright future.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to further friendly cooperation in all
fields.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, who is also the vice-chairman of the Military
Commission of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China and a state councillor, said that although China is far away
from Belarus, the Chinese people share traditional friendship with
the people of Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the profound concern of the leaders of the two
countries, the development of friendly ties between China and
Belarus has been steady, smooth and healthy in politics, economics
and trade, science and technology and culture in recent years, he
said.
</P>
<P>
China is ready to maintain and deepen friendly cooperation
between the two countries on the basis of the five principles of
peaceful co-existence, he added.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian arrived in Minsk Sunday on an official visit to
Belarus.  
</P>
