<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Uzbekistan Forge Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Uzbekistan have signed a
protocol on establishing diplomatic relations between the two
countries, according to reports here today.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus News Agency said the protocol was signed by the
ambassadors of Cyprus and Uzbekistan to the Russian Federation,
Platon Kyriakides and Shamansur Shakhalilov, respectively. But it
didn't say when and where.
</P>
<P>
Local reports said Shakhalilov described the agreement as
"historic" and expressed Uzbekistan's readiness to develop close
and friendly ties with Cyprus in all fields. He noted that Cyprus is
the 101st country with which Uzbekistan has forged diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
On his part, the Cypriot ambassador was quoted as saying
that the official signing of the protocol will reinforce the
already friendly relations between Cyprus and Uzbekistan. 
