<HEADLINE> Malaria Awareness Exhibition Mounted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe today mounted a malaria
awareness exhibition at the on-going 33rd Organization of African
Unity (OAU) summit.
</P>
<P>
Exhibitors included the government, private sector companies
and the World Health Organization (WHO).
</P>
<P>
The OAU Council of Ministers at the weekend adopted a malaria
declaration, calling for the intensification of control and
prevention programs.
</P>
<P>
"The exhibition aims to enhance the discussions going on about
malaria and find ways of coming up with a combined effort on
prevention and control," a spokesperson for Zimbabwe's Ministry
of Health said.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 percent of all malaria cases are in sub-Saharan
Africa and some 2.7 million people die of malaria every year.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition shows available preventive measures like
spraying and protective clothing as well as cures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
