<HEADLINE> Czech Deputy Foreign Minister to Visit Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A three-man delegation from
the Republic of Czech is expected to arrive here on June 9 for a
two-day working visit.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued here today by the Ministry of
Foreign Affairs, the delegation shall be led by Czech's Deputy
Foreign Minister Helena Bambasova and is to hold official talks
with Tanzanian Foreign Minister Jakaya Kikwete.
</P>
<P>
This is the first official delegation to visit Tanzania
since the rise of the republics Czech and Slovakia after the the
peaceful division of the former Socialist Republic of
Czechslovakia in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The statement said relations between Tanzania and Czech under
the former Czechslovakia Republic took off in 1975 following the
signing of an economic co-operation between the two countries and
another one in 1986 which was specific on trade.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania received various types of assistance from the former
socialist republic including plant and machinery for cement and
ceramic industries and the rehabilitation of the Tanzania
Breweries Limited.
</P>
<P>
The visit of the deputy foreign minister to Tanzania is
expected to be an opportunity for the sharing of experience of
the two countries on the on-going political and economic
transformation especially as Czech is famous for its highly
advanced fish farming. 
</P>
</TEXT>
