<HEADLINE> PA Official Denys Involvement In Killings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian officials today
categorically denied Israeli charges that the Palestinian
Authority was behind the killings of three Palestinians who have
allegedly sold land to Jews.
</P>
<P>
According to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service
based in East Jerusalem, Hanan Ashrawi, Member of Palestinian
Council and Minister of Higher Education, said the killings of the
three Palestinian land dealers were possibly of criminal nature
and not an issue that the Palestinian Authority took decision on.
</P>
<P>
In the past few weeks, three Palestinian land dealers were
found dead in the West Bank. Israel has held the Palestinian
Authority responsible for the killings.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Benyamin Netanayhu held a meeting here this
morning to discuss the matter. A statement issued by Netanyahu's
Media Adviser David Bar-Ilan indicated Israel will launch an
international propaganda campaign against what it called
infringements by the Palestinian Authority of human rights and of
the Oslo peace accords.
</P>
<P>
However, Ashrawi declared "our only position was that it did
not allow the sale of land to Israelis," and "it is a question of
(Palestinian) sovereignty."
</P>
<P>
She said that the Palestinian Authority inherited the Jordanian
law in the West Bank and other systems in Gaza and the existing
law does allow the death penalty, but has not been implemented.
</P>
<P>
"I can say categorically that the Palestinian Authority did
not give any order to carry out any death penalty or to carry out
any execution of killings," she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
