<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Help Monitor Algerian Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africa has sent a team
of observers to Algeria to help monitor elections which are
scheduled for June 5, the Foreign Affairs Department of South
Africa said today.
</P>
<P>
The team comprises two representatives from the Foreign
Affairs Department and one each from the Institute for Democracy
in South Africa and the Parliamentary Foreign Affairs Portfolio
Committee, the department said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The four will join an Organization of African Unity (OAU)
team, which has been accredited to observe the Algerian
elections. International observers will also be sent from the
United Nations and the League of Arab States.
</P>
<P>
Since it became a member of the OAU in May 1994, South Africa
has sent election observers to Cote d'Ivoire, Niger, Uganda,
Tanzania, Ethiopia, Comoros, Sao Tome and Principe, Algeria and
Sudan.
</P>
<P>
This practice is consistent with South Africa's commitment to
promoting the democratization process on the African continent,
the statement said. 
