<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Sees Great Loss to Animal Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Agriculture of
Ethiopia today said it loses an estimated 1.5 to 2.5 billion Birr
(about 223 to 373 million Dollars) annually as many of animals
die each year due to diseases.
</P>
<P>
This is disclosed here by Hadira Gebru, head of the Animal and
Fishery Resources Development Department of the ministry when she
was opening the one-day annual meeting of the Ethiopian Assistant
Veterinarians Association.
</P>
<P>
Hadira said that about 150,000 square kilometers of land in
the southern and western Ethiopia is infested with tse-tse fly.
</P>
<P>
It is increasingly proving difficult to carry out any form of
agriculture in these localities due to the inavailability of
animal power, she said.
</P>
<P>
She urged participants of the meeting to come up with concrete
solutions to the problem which she said poses considerable
challenge to the development of Ethiopia's animal resources.
</P>
