recommended a six-month renewal of the oil-for-food deal once it
expires on June 7.
</P>
<P>
Under U.N. Security Council Resolution 986, the Iraqi
government could sell 2 billion dollars worth of oil over a
six-month period to buy food and medicine for its people. 
