<HEADLINE> US Lockheed Martin Planning Russian Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Lockheed Martin Corporation, a
big military aircraft maker of the United States, announced today
that it is forming a joint venture with a Russian organization,
Intersputnik, to offer satellite communications services.
</P>
<P>
The company, to be called Lockheed Martin Intersputnik, intends
to initially provide broadcast telecommunications to Eastern
Europe, Africa, parts of Asia and the former Soviet Union.
Eventually, it plans to offer direct-to-home video, audio and
mobile services worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The venture is the latest move by Lockheed Martin to strengthen
its ties with Russia which has considerable expertise in rocket
and satellite technology, according to a report of the New York
Times today.
</P>
<P>
Intersputnik, whose full name is the Intersputnik International
Organization of Space Communications, has 22 member countries and
operates a satellite communications system.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will be based in London and have a marketing
office in Moscow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
