<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London Ends Well Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in Europe
ended mixed today, with London finishing well down while Paris
recovering from a drastic fall after Sunday's Socialist election
victory.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE-100 index of leading shares chalked up its
biggest one-day decline in point terms for two months as bank
stocks tumbled and fears grew of a possible rise in British
interest rates. It closed down 58.5 points at 4,562.8.
</P>
<P>
Paris stocks ended with healthy gains after a day of
roller-coaster trading with investors trying to second-guess the
impact of the new socialist-led government on business. The CAC-40
index closed up 17.71 points to 2,601.45.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German shares ended up nearly two percent with
the export sector boosted by the stronger dollar. The 30-share DAX
index closed at 3,605.62 up 57.78 points. 
</P>
