<HEADLINE> Nato-led Reserve Force Officers Tour Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Nato-led Stablization Force(SFOR)
said on Monday that senior officers from its backup forces are
visiting Bosnia this week on a reconnaissance tour.
</P>
<P>
"This reconnaissance is designed to enable them to gain a clear
picture of the requirements should Nato decide to deploy the SFOR
Strategic Reserve(SSR)," SFOR Spokesman Major Chris Riley said.
</P>
<P>
SSR consists of troops from Nato and non-Nato nations, which
are dployed in their own countries, but will come to Bosnia to
assist SFOR if required by SFOR commander and approved by Nato's
supreme command.
</P>
<P>
During the seven-day visit, the SSR officers will meet with
their SFOR counterparts, receive briefings and visit SFOR bases
across Bosnia, Riley said. 
</P>
