<HEADLINE> IFC Invest $42 Mln in Indonesian Shipping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the approval of 42 million U.S.
dollars in loan and equity financing on its own account for
Indonesia's shipping company.
</P>
<P>
The PT Berlian Laju Tanker (BLT) is one of the country's
largest shipping companies specializing in carrying oil products,
asphalt, edible oils, chemicals and liquefied petroleum gas.
</P>
<P>
IFC's financing will help the company to expand its fleet in
the international and regional markets and reduce the age of the
existing fleet.
</P>
<P>
This is IFC's second shipping investment in Indonesia and its
first internationally syndicated loan to an Indonesian shipping
company to acquire vessels to be operated under the Indonesian
flag.
</P>
<P>
IFC's financing includes a loan of 22 million dollars for its
own account and an equity investment of 20 million dollars.
Besides, it will prepare a syndicated loan of 68 million dollars,
co-arranged by MeesPerson N.V., for participating international
commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and the largest
multilateral source of equity and loan financing for private
sector projects in developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
