<HEADLINE> Britain Urges its Nationals to Leave Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The British government has strongly
called on its citizens to leave the war-stricken Sierra Leone,
saying there would be no further evacuation attempts.
</P>
<P>
A British Foreign Office spokesman said in a statement issued
this afternoon, "The British High Commission in Freetown (capital
city) is closed. The American aircraft carrier Kearsage is
organizing an evacuation which is currently underway from the Cape
Sierra Hotel in Freetown."
</P>
<P>
"All British and American nationals who think it is safe to do
so should make their way to the Cape Sierra Hotel as soon as
possible," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Office also stressed, "There will be no further
evacuation. The British High Commission staff will leave Freetown
with this evacuation."
</P>
<P>
The African country is quickly sliding into a state of anarchy
when Nigerian gunboats bombarded Freetown in an effort to restore
Sierra Leone's ousted president. 
</P>
