<HEADLINE> 43 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Forty-three rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed in military
operations in southeastern Turkey in the past week, an official
statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued today by the office of the Emergency
Regional Rule, said that five Turkish military personnel,
including four village guards, also died in the clashes between
government troops and PKK militants.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the security forces captured four PKK
members, and 11 PKK guerrillas surrendered to the government
troops in the region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Turkish cross-border military operation, which
started on May 14, has been continuing in northern Iraq in a bid
to sweep the PKK out of the region.
</P>
<P>
More than 23,000 people including PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops have been killed in conflicts since the PKK
staged a separatist war for self-rule in eastern and
southeastern Turkey in August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
