<HEADLINE> Greek President Meets Visiting Chinese Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Greek President Costis
Stephanopoulos and visiting Chinese leader Li Ruihuan today
expressed the hope that the two countries will enhance their
friendship.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting here this afternoon, Li Ruihuan, chairman
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), conveyed to the Greek president
an invitation from Chinese President Jiang Zemin to visit
China. Stephanopoulos accepted.
</P>
<P>
Li said that since the establishment of diplomatic relations
between China and Greece 25 years ago, the two countries have
witnessed a steady development of friendship and cooperation in
politics, economy and science and technology.
</P>
<P>
With frequent exchanges of high-level visits, the two countries
have improved mutual understanding and enhanced friendship and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking highly of the sound cooperation between the two
countries in international affairs, Li thanked Greece for its
support to China, especially Greece's adherence to the "one-China"
policy and supporting China in its efforts to join the World Trade
Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
Stephanopoulos said he believes that Li's current visit will
not only strengthen the existing good relations between the two
countries, but also help further Greece-China ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that his visit to China in 1982 had deeply impressed
him, and that he admired greatly the achievements made by China in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that as a major world power, China will
play an increasingly important role in international affairs and
human progress.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan noted that China and Greece, two ancient
civilizations, had made special contributions to the formation of
human civilization.
</P>
<P>
Echoing Li's views, Stephanopoulos said that one civilization
should not be allowed to impose itself on others. He said the
civilizations of Greece and China have many points in common.
</P>
