<HEADLINE> Pak-India Talks to Be of Elementary Nature: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The foreign secretary-level talks
between Pakistan and India, scheduled to take place here on June
18 and 19, will be of a "very elementary nature" -- paving the way
for further dialogue, a Pakistani official said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We are busy in preparing blueprints for these talks" and no
headway is expected at this stage, Abbas Haider, director general
of the Policy Planning Division of the Pakistani Foreign Ministry,
told reporters at a briefing.
</P>
<P>
In answering a question, he said the reopening of the Indian
Consulate in Karachi might be on India's agenda, but it is
certainly not on the agenda of his country.
</P>
<P>
"We have taken the initiative and are now on record that
Pakistan wants parleys with India and is ready to resolve issues
by dialogue," Haider added.  
