<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Graf Bowed out of French Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Steffi Graf was
beaten in straight sets in the quarterfinals at the French Open
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The second-ranked, five-time champion German was pulled down by
11th-seeded Amanda Coetzer of South Africa 6-1, 6-4, failing to
make the semifinals for the first time since 1986 at Roland Garros.
</P>
<P>
By beating Graf for the third time of the year, Coetzer has
become Graf's nemesis and reached the first Grand Slam semifinal
of her career.
</P>
<P>
The South African gave Graf her first defeat at the Australian
Open and humiliated the German her worst defeat of 6-0, 6-1 at the
German Open last month.
</P>
<P>
Of the 78 points Coetzer won in one hour and 32 minutes, 64
came on unforced errors by Graf, the winner of the tournament in
the last two years.
</P>
<P>
"I was very nervous. I started off making a lot of mistakes, I
was unsure of my shots," said Graf, winner of 21 Grand Slam titles.
</P>
<P>
The match was interrupted for 45 minutes by rain with Coetzer
up 3-1 in the second set.  
</P>
</TEXT>
