<HEADLINE> Austria To Bid for Euro 2004 Soccer with Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian government announced
its full back on Tuesday for a joint bid to host the 2004 European
soccer championship with Hungary.
</P>
<P>
Chancellor Viktor Klima said the government would support the
bid with 1.5 to two billion Austrian schillings (123.3 million to
164.4 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Austrian soccer federation (OeFB) press spokesman Heinz
Palme said the Austrian and Hungarian federations would meet in
two weeks, and the Hungarian government has pledged financial
support for the joint bid.
</P>
<P>
European soccer's governing body UEFA is expected to make a
decision on bids in 1998. Spain is considered a leading contender.
</P>
<P>
Belgium and the Netherlands will be the first joint hosts in
2000. 
