<HEADLINE> Thailand to Launch Education Reform Program in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will launch a nationwide
education reform program next year to improve people's access to
education, while urging them to realize the value of education.
</P>
<P>
The program is aimed at promoting the fundamental education for
Thais and improving the efficiency and orientation of the
education management at various levels to meet the social and
economic needs and help enhance Thailand's ability of
self-reliance, according to the Thai Government House.
</P>
<P>
The program also calls for Thai teenagers to realize the
importance of education, the Government House said in a press
release issued today.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet approved 100 million baht (4 million U.S.
dollars) at its weekly meeting today for publicizing the program.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet also approved guidelines to encourage and boost
self-learning among Thais, while urging institutes of higher
learning to organize more non-degree programs and curriculums for
the public.  
</P>
