<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Meets With Macao High Court President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chen Ziying, deputy director of the
Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council, meeting
today with the Macao High Court President Manuel Antonio Maduro,
said that China and Portugal have had fine cooperation since the
signing of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration on the Macao
question.
</P>
<P>
Chen added that both want to maintain the economic prosperity
and social stability of Macao.
</P>
<P>
Frequent visits by high-level leaders of the two countries also
help increase their cooperation on the Macao question, he said,
pointing out that, after China resumes the exercise of its
sovereignty over Macao, it will implement the 'one country, two
systems' principle to the letter.
</P>
<P>
Macao will continue to maintain its capitalist system and
lifestyle, and its laws will remain unchanged by and large, he
said, and the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) will enjoy
the power of executive decision, legislative rights, and an
independent judiciary.
</P>
<P>
No central or local governments will interfere in the Macao
SAR's affairs, according to the Basic Law of the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
Maduro spoke about the work done by the Portugese Macao
government on localizing the law and training judges, and pledged
to increase cooperation with the Chinese side and contribute to a
smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived in Beijing on May 31, at the invitation
of the China Association of Judges (CAJ). 
</P>
</TEXT>
