<HEADLINE> Modern Medical Center Established in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Work on the biggest medical center
in Asia was finished today in Shanghai, China's largest metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The 34-story Shanghai Changzheng Hospital was built at a cost
of 43.5 million US dollars. The funding came from the local
Changzheng Hospital and a Hong Kong company.
</P>
<P>
The facility will be used for medical treatment, teaching, and
research, and has modern telecommunications, and a heli-pad on the
roof, served by high-speed elevators.
</P>
<P>
The building has a central oxygen system supplying every ward,
which are also supplied with telephones, televisions, fax
machines, washrooms, and advanced medical equipment.
</P>
<P>
It also has extremely clean rooms for operations with the most
advanced monitoring systems.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin did the calligraphic work for the
hospital's name.  
</P>
