<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Destroys Heroin, "Ice" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China burned 500 kilograms of
heroin and "ice" today in the town of Humen in Guangdong Province,
in a move to crack down on drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the China National Narcotics Commission (CNNC) and
the Guangdong provincial government put the torch to the drugs,
while some 15,000 locals looked on in blistering afternoon heat.
</P>
<P>
It was on this day 158 years ago, that Li Zexu, a national
hero, burned 1.15 million kilograms of opium also in exactly the
same town, an incident that triggered a two-year Opium War with
Britain, the result of which was that China was forced to sign the
Treaty of Nanking and cede Hong Kong island to Britain.
</P>
<P>
Bai Jingfu, deputy director of the CNNC, said, "We shall never
forget the horrendous disasters drugs brought to the Chinese
nation, and we shall never allow historical tragedies to repeat
themselves."  
</P>
</TEXT>
