<HEADLINE> Beijing's First Professional Consultants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's first 344 professional
consultants received their registration certificates today, as the
first group to be registered here.
</P>
<P>
The papers are issued by the Beijing Consulting Association,
which plays a guiding and coordinating role in the field in
science and technology, which first appeared in the Chinese
capital in 1979, when the Beijing Municipal Association of Science
and Technology set up a consultation department.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, Beijing had 4,758 consultation agencies
with 140,000 employees, 49,200 of whom were consultants.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 alone, these agencies were involved in 539,000 projects
and earned 6.27 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, the central government designated Beijing as a pilot
city in developing the sector. 
</P>
