economic cooperation, jointly organized by respective bilateral
economic committees of the two countries, ended here today after
discussions on ways and means to enhance such cooperation.
</P>
<P>
It was the first of its kind ever held in Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The Japan-Myanmar Economic Committee comprises 65 leading
industrialists while the Myanmar-Japan Economic Committee is
formed by officials of the Ministry of National Planning and
Economic Development.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Japan's Chamber of Commerce and Industry (CCL)
reached a memorandum of understanding here with its Myanmar
counterpart in April to enhance its investment and cooperation in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Japan's investment in Myanmar amounted to over 192 million U.S.
dollars in 13 permitted projects out of a total foreign investment
of over 6 billion dollars from 21 countries and regions at the end
of March this year, according to the latest official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Japan, a major donor to Myanmar in the past, is also a major
creditor nation for the country, which has debts up to 400 billion
yen (about 3.3 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to a latest official report, the Japanese government
extended to Myanmar today for the 18th time a grant-in-aid of 2
billion yen (about 16 million dollars), to be used for debt
relief.  
</P>
