<HEADLINE> Chinese, Turkish Procurators-General Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Siqing, the
procurator-general of the Supreme People's Procuratorate held
talks this afternoon with Vural Savas, the Supreme Public Attorney
General of Turkey's Highest Court of Appeal on judicial matters.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that although countries all have their own national
situation, their judiciary face the same task of maintaining
national security, social stability, and a peaceful life for their
citizens.
</P>
<P>
Each country should establish a legal system according to its
own national situation, he noted, but that it is also very
important to learn from each other.
</P>
<P>
Savas agreed with Zhang. He also expressed his thanks to Zhang,
saying that during this visit he has been deeply impressed by
China's reforms and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
Savas arrived in Beijing yesterday. He is on a good-will visit
to China as Zhang's guest, and is expected to leave Beijing
tomorrow for Xi'an, the capital of northwest China's Shaanxi
Province. 
