<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 30.67 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market gained 30.67 points today to reach
3838.85 as against the overnight close of 3808.18.
</P>
<P>
The National Index also rose further by 10.67 points to 1644.84
from 1634.17 yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The sustained rally in a select few heavy-weight scrips pushed
the Sensitive Index on the BSE market further up on fresh buying
support from local operators and foreign institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The BSE Sensitive Index started better at 3810.63 and moved
upward to touch the intra-day high of 3864.41 before settling down
at 3838.85.
</P>
<P>
Hind Lever, Telco, MTNL and Larsen Toubro recorded smart rises
on buying support while GE Ship, Icici, Ranbaxy and Reliance
Industries finished subdued.  
</P>
</TEXT>
