<HEADLINE> Dewulf Sails to French Open Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Filip Dewulf became the first Belgian
to ever secure a semifinal spot at the French Open when he breezed
past his Swedish opponent here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On the center court, the Belgian qualifier outwitted Magnus
Norman 6-2, 6-7 (2/7), 6-4 and 6-3 in 2 hours 43 minutes.
</P>
<P>
He will play either Russian defending champion Yevgeny
Kafelnikov or 20-year-old Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten to vie for a
spot in Sunday's final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
