<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwestern Chinese City Presents Hong Kong With Sculpture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A sculpture from Chongqing,
China's fourth municipality directly under the central government,
was sent to the Hong Kong today on the occasion of Hong Kong's
coming return its motherland.
</P>
<P>
The sculpture is entitled "Auspicious Color Silk" and gives a
strong sense of motion, suggesting the movement of the Yangtze
River to the sea, and the return of Hong Kong to the motherland
after more than a hundred years of ups and downs.
</P>
<P>
Leaves dotting the sculpture signal vitality. Hong Kong's
flower, the bauhinia, and Chongqing's flower, the azalea, are
carved on the base.
</P>
<P>
It weighs 800 kg and stands 3.6 m. high. It is the work of
artists of the Sichuan Academy of Fine Arts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
