<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rain Saves Graf at French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Steffi Graf was
plunged into deep trouble but rain saved her at the moment at the
French Open as her quarterfinal was halted on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Graf committed an incredible 45 unforced errors as she lost
eight of the nine first games and was trailing Amanda Coetzer of
South Africa 1-6, 3-1 when the match was stopped by a light
drizzle.
</P>
<P>
Coetzer, who had never sailed further than the fourth round in
eight previous appearances, has beaten Graf twice in their last
three matches.
</P>
<P>
The German who ranked second was facing the prospect of her
first defeat at Roland Garros since the 1994 semifinals when she
was beaten by Mary Pierce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
