<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Carnival for Youth's Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A carnival is to be organized
here on June 14 to commend the youth's contribution to society and
to encourage them to renew their efforts in helping build a better
future for Hong Kong after the handover.
</P>
<P>
Director of Home Affairs Shelley Lau told a press conference
today that the carnival is one of the many community-building
activities organized by her department to complement the handover
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"As Hong Kong is entering a new era and the youth are always
regarded as the 'pillar of society', the youth are playing an even
more important role in the development of the territory," Lau
said.
</P>
<P>
She said the carnival is aimed at encouraging the youth to
participate more in community activities to create a better future
for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The carnival will comprise booth games, an exhibition and a
variety show.  
</P>
</TEXT>
