<HEADLINE> PLA General Meets With Cuban Military Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- General Zhang Wannian,
Vice-Chairman of China's Central Military Commission, met here
today with a military delegation headed by Lieutenant General
Nestor Lopez Cuba, director of the General Political Department of
Revolutionary Armed Forces of Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to the delegation, Zhang said that the
frequent exchange of visits between the military leaders of the
two countries in recent years has promoted understanding and
friendship of the two armed forces and has helped strengthen the
friendship and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Zhang briefed the Cuban visitors on China's current situation
of reform and opening-up to the outside world. He also expressed
his appreciation and thanks to Cuba for its support to China in
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Lopez told Zhang that the delegation was deeply impressed by
China's reform and opening-up policy and the country's economic
achievement. Cuba could draw on China's successful experience, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Lopez expressed his hope that the people of the two countries
and their armed forces would continue to increase their exchanges
and friendship.
</P>
<P>
Lopez and his party are here as guests of the General Political
Department of Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA). 
</P>
</TEXT>
