<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Leader Meets With Colombian Conservative Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a Standing Committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, meeting with a delegation of the
Colombian Conservative Party today, said that since China and
Colombia forged diplomatic ties in 1980 bilateral relations have
grown smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Economic and trade co-operation has expanded, he said, and the
two countries have supported each other in international affairs,
he said, adding that further strengthening this will benefit the
development of the two countries and is in the interest of their
peoples.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, expressed his appreciation for the Colombian
Conservative Party's consistent effort to safeguard national
sovereignty and national independence, promote social development,
and improve Sino-Colombian relations.
</P>
<P>
The CPC is willing to increase friendly contacts and
co-operation with the Columbian Conservative Party based on the
four principles of party-to-party relations, he said, adding that
he hopes the two parties will make a joint effort to establish
long-term and stable bilateral friendly relations oriented with
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The president of the Conservative Party, Fabio Valencia, who
led the delegation, expressed his appreciation for China's great
achievements in recent years.
</P>
<P>
China has scored great economic development, he said, Changes
have taken place in people's mental outlook.
</P>
<P>
China, as an influential country in the world, can provide
experience for Columbia and other developing countries as well, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
"We are willing to increase contacts with the CPC and to make
concerted efforts for the development of bilateral ties," he said.
</P>
<P>
Valencia and his delegation are here as guests of the
International Department of the CPC Central Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
