<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5 killed, 6 Injured By Rebel Mine In North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and six
others injured today by a rebel mine in the Northern province of
Sri Lanka, according to informed sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) set off a mine as a bus traveling from Madagal to Jaffna
City carrying civilians escorted by the army and police passed by.
</P>
<P>
Two army soldiers, one policeman and two civilians were killed
while one policeman and five civilians were injured in the mine
blast.
</P>
<P>
The injured were sent to the Jaffna Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a guerrilla war since 1983 against
the Sri Lankan government for a separate Tamil state in the north
and east of the island country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
