<HEADLINE> China Selecting Cities With Best Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China will choose a number of model
cities that have the county's best urban environment, the State
Bureau of Environmental Protection announced today.
</P>
<P>
The bureau will examine cities' capability of sustainable
development, the level of their social and economic development,
their environmental quality, and level of their environmental
controls. Any city is eligible for participation.
</P>
<P>
Zhangjiagang in east China's Jiangsu Province was given the
title of "China's Model Environmental City" last year. Experts say
that Zhuhai in Guangdong Province, Xiamen in Fujian Province, and
Dalian in Liaoning Province have reached high levels in terms of
social and economic development and environmental quality. "With
further efforts, they may be chosen as model cities," experts say.
</P>
<P>
The result of the selection process is expected to be announced
later this year.  
</P>
