<HEADLINE> Mongolia's Proven Gold Reserves Reach 1,300 tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia has announced it has
proven gold deposits of 1,300 tons and hopes to become one of the
world's top 20 gold producers with an annual output of 20 tons by
the year 2000, media reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The government is now planning to attract foreign investment to
boost exploration in gold-rich areas like Govi-Altai, Hovsgol,
Omnogovi, Dornogovi and Bayan-Hongol to aid the revitalization of
the economy, reports quoted experts as saying.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that Mongolia, which produced 5.4 tons of gold
in 1996 and expects to produce 7 tons this year, has geological
gold reserves which are possibly several times higher than the
proven reserves. 
</P>
