<HEADLINE> HK New Airport Awards New Contracts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Airport Authority
(AA) has awarded two new contracts at the new airport at Chek Lap
Kok.
</P>
<P>
A release from the AA today said Thorn Lighting Ltd. of the
United Kingdom has been awarded a 205 million HK dollar (26.3
million U.S. dollars) contract to provide airfield ground lighting
for the Northern Runway.
</P>
<P>
The works mainly comprise the design, manufacture, supply,
delivery, installation, testing and commissioning of the airfield
ground lighting for the runway and associated taxiways and
integration with the Southern Runway system.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Safegate International AB of Sweden has been awarded
a 48.4 million HK dollar (6.2 million U.S. dollars) contract to
provide aircraft parking aid at the passenger terminal building.
</P>
<P>
The works comprise the supply, installation, testing,
commissioning and maintenance of aircraft parking aid at each of
the 38 frontal aircraft stands for the passenger terminal building
and 27 remote stands to be provided at airport opening in April
1998, plus the additional 10 frontal stands to be provided when
the passenger terminal building's northwest concourse extension is
completed.
</P>
<P>
The equipment enables aircraft to position themselves correctly
in preparation for loading and unloading.  
</P>
