<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dortmund Club President Quits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Borussia Dortmund president Gerd
Niebaum said on Tuesday that he planned to step down from the post
which he had held for 11 years.
</P>
<P>
Niebaum, 48, explained that the burden as club president was
too heavy and he was not to sacrifice his family since he was also
in charge of a law office in the town.
</P>
<P>
"I've put in between eight and 10 hours a day for the club,
gladly and passionately, but with the growing burdens of the role
I do not want to sacrifice my family and professional life for a
further three years," he said.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Dortmund won the European Cup crown. "I wouldn't
have arrived at this decision had we not won the final last
Wednesday," Niebaum said.
</P>
<P>
Niebaum was the president when the club won the 1989 German Cup
and two German championships in 1995 and 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
