<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Model Steel, Iron Company Setting New Goal (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The success of the Handan Iron and Steel Company has inspired
state-owned enterprises still suffering from economic losses to
take reform measures.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 people from across the country came to
Handan Iron and Steel Company to study the successful experience
or attend training courses there from 1992 to 1996, according to
Chairman Liu Hanzhang.
</P>
<P>
Liu, also mastermind of the experiment, explained his company
has been practising the method of deciding on production costs by
first taking market prices into account, replacing the traditional
way of first calculating production costs and expected profits,
and then setting market prices, which had been popular under the
planned economic mode.
</P>
<P>
Through the use of this simulating method, a market mechanism
has been introduced into the interior management of an enterprise,
making every employee directly feel the pressure of market
competition, and enabling them to become market-aware and
eventually to take the initiative to participate in market
competition, Liu went on.
</P>
<P>
Before this, state-owned enterprises had been operating under a
plan that included pre-set production costs and prices; and
pulling along in early 1980s by calculating profits in advance,
with enterprises authorized to independently market five percent
of their respective output.
</P>
<P>
In the 1990s, state-owned enterprises were put to face the
market more directly by themselves and were given the right to
control selling 95 percent of their output.
</P>
<P>
The Handan Iron and Steel Company has grown into one of China's
18 to enterprises and increased the value of its total assets from
2.2 billion yuan to 8.83 billion yuan. State-owned assets of the
company have multiplied by 8.2 times and has brought down the
ratio of debt to assets from 70 percent to 39.22 percent.
</P>
<P>
As the new goal is set, the Handan Iron and Steel Company,
which primarily turns out steel used as building materials, still
has to work very hard to attain it, said Liu.
</P>
<P>
He added that his company will strive to catch up with the
Baoshan Iron and Steel Company of Shanghai, Shoudu Iron and Steel
Company of Beijing, two iron and steel production giants in
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970603.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Model Steel, Iron Company Sets New Goal (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANDAN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Handan Iron and Steel Company of
north China's Hebei Province plans to earn over 10 billion yuan
from sales annually by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Liu Hanzhang, chairman of the company's board, made known his
company's new goal during an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The Handan Iron and Steel Company, cited as a model enterprise
in China, produces steel sheets, as well as wire stock, steel
bars, and structural steel, with technology imported from Germany
and equipment imported from France.
</P>
<P>
The once little-known Handan Iron and Steel Complex, which is
state-owned enterprise, has transformed itself from a money-losing
enterprise into a big profit maker.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1958, the Handan Iron and Steel Company with a work
force of 28,000, had been on a losing streak until 1990. After
replacing its method of counting costs and working out expected
interest levels before setting prices for its products, the
company was able to fix acceptable market prices, and work out its
own definitive production costs.
</P>
<P>
If a production unit, overran production costs, it was seen as
failing to make a profit, thus affecting bonuses and wages for its
employees. If workers reduced both production costs and market
prices, they were rewarded.
</P>
<P>
The method has worked. The complex netted in 700 million yuan
of profits in 1996, compared to only one million yuan in 1990. It
used to suffer losses in 26 of the 28 kinds of rolled steel it
produced. But in 1995, it ranked second among the country's 45
iron and steel companies in terms of comprehensive economic
performance.
</P>
<P>
After the success of the Handan experiment, state-owned
enterprises have been urged to learn how to thrive in a
competitive market from the Handan company's operations as the
country is trying to invigorate its state-owned enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
