<HEADLINE> Share Prices Almost Steady on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices fluctuated in a
narrow range on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index gained 0.32 points to close at 2061.22
today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume increased to 145.81 million units, valued
at 380.76 million Singapore dollars (about 266.27 million U.S.
dollars). Declines led advances by 218 to 108, while 297 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Westmont Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 26.41 million units. It was followed by
Benefun which had 15.19 million shares traded. Labroy was next
with 5.82 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Malaya Banking and Malaya Banking 200 shared the top spot on
the gainers' list as each of them rose 70 cents to finish at 15.5
dollars respectively. Creative 50 gained 60 cents to end at 25.7
Singapore dollars, while the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS)
Foreign closed 40 cents higher at 18.9 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign was
the biggest loser as it declined 80 cents to end at 28.6 Singapore
dollars. The Bukit Sembawang, Keppel Corporation, and the Overseas
Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign each fell 20 cents to
close at 27.8, 6.35, and 18.2 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
