<HEADLINE> Indian Prime Minister to Visit Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister I. K.
Gujral is scheduled to visit Nepal from June 5 for enhancing
cooperation between the two countries, official sources said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The three-day visit, the first by an Indian prime minister in
the past five years, assumes significance as India and Nepal would
exchange the instrument of ratification of the Mahakali Treaty
concerning the integrated development of the Mahakali River
flowing over the two neighboring countries. The treaty was signed
by the two countries last year.
</P>
<P>
Under the treaty, India will supply 300 cusecs of water from
Tanakpur in Uttar Pradesh in the dry season and 70 million units
of power to Nepal free of charge.
</P>
<P>
Gujral is also expected to sign a power trade agreement with
Nepal during his visit. Nepal, which has the potential of 83,000
mw of hydropower, has signed an umbrella agreement with India
selling its power to India.
</P>
<P>
Gujral will meet Nepalese King Birendra and hold talks with his
Nepalese counterpart, Lokendra B. Chand, on the two countries'
relations. The two countries are also expected to expand their
cooperation in other fields, the same sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
