<HEADLINE> Macao New 10-Pataca Coin Greeted With Reluctance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A new coin which was put into
circulation on Monday has been left in the cold as most local
residents prefer banknotes to coins.
</P>
<P>
The 10-pataca coin, issued for the first time, was inconvenient
to carry along, many residents said.
</P>
<P>
With gold and silver colors on the face, the coin is bigger
than Hong Kong's 10-dollar coin. It depicts a church on one side
and the word "Macao" in Chinese and Portuguese on the other.
</P>
<P>
A total of 20 million pieces of the coin will be issued via the
Bank of China's Macao Branch and another note-issuing bank in the
territory.
</P>
<P>
Macao now has six kinds of coins, including 10 cents, 20 cents,
50 cents, 1 pataca, 5 patacas and 10 patacas.
</P>
<P>
The 10-pataca banknote will continue to be in circulation until
the government orders a ban on its use.  
</P>
</TEXT>
