<HEADLINE> Hongkong Telecom Sponsors Satellite Service for Handover Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Telecom (HKT), a full
service telecom provider, announced here today that it will
sponsor satellite service to uplink the 96 hours of non-stop world
feed for handover celebration activities.
</P>
<P>
From 10 p.m. June 29 to 10 p.m. July 3, Hongkong Telecom will
provide satellite transmission for a series of reunification
programs and celebration activities organized by the Association
for the Celebration of the Reunification of Hong Kong with China
(ACRHKC) and other non-governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony between HKT and ACRHKC, Hongkong
Telecom Chief Executive Linus Cheung said, "At Hongkong Telecom,
we not only share with everyone in Hong Kong the joy of the
reunification of Hong Kong with China, we are also proud of taking
part in enabling billions of others around the world to share the
joyful historic moment."
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan, representing ACRHKC, said, "Through the 96 hours of
world feed, we will fully project the joy, hope and vitality of
people in Hong Kong as they celebrate the arrival of a new era. We
believe that the world will feel the true spirit of Hong Kong
through the transmission."
</P>
<P>
The world feed signal will be uplinked digitally via three
satellites -- Intelsat 66, Intelsat 180 and AsiaSat 2 -- covering
the Pacific and Indian Ocean regions. Hongkong Telecom will
provide one video channel and three audio channels for the
transmission of these events, which will be able to reach
two-thirds of the world directly and the rest of the world
indirectly.  
</P>
</TEXT>
