<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Takes Tough Stance on Relations With Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The 15 foreign ministers of the
European Union member nations agreed Monday in Luxembourg to keep
their ambassadors away from Tehran unless Iran is ready to allow
all the envoys back.
</P>
<P>
They reached the decision at the ministers' monthly meeting.
The ambassadors they referred to also included the German and
Danish envoys who were told by Iran in April not to return.
</P>
<P>
The EU countries withdrew their ambassadors from Iran after a
German court ruling on April 10 that the Iranian government backed
the 1992 assassination of four Iranian dissidents in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
When the envoys decided to return to Tehran, Iran told the
German and Danish ambassadors to stay home, citing as reason what
it called their governments' anti-Iran views. None of the EU
envoys returned as a result.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers agreed that none would return to Tehran
as long as Iran was not ready to welcome back all the 15
EU ambassadors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
