by hanging himself last Sunday inside the detention cell of the
Ninoy Aquino International Airport (NAIA) after being detained for
traffic violation.
</P>
<P>
In a handwritten note to Toledo, President Ramos also asked him
to enlist the support of other government agencies to facilitate
the investigation.
</P>
<P>
According to the local media, NAIA General Manager Francisco
Atayde has sought the expeditious investigation of the incident to
determine the real cause of Quinoto's death.  
