<HEADLINE> 6 Policemen, 3 Others Killed by Rebels in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- At least six policemen and three
others were killed by Tamil rebels on Monday when they were
patrolling in the Eastern province of Sri Lanka, according to
military sources here today.
</P>
<P>
Police personnel were ambushed by rebels of the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) on Monday evening when they were on
patrol at Valachchenai in Batticaloa district in the province.
</P>
<P>
During the confrontation, at least six policemen and three home
guards were killed and one policeman injured, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a guerrilla war for an
independent Tamil state in the north and east of the country since
1983.  
</P>
