<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Enterprises in East China Province Increase Competitiveness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Major enterprises in east China's
Jiangsu Province, already an economic powerhouse, have increased
their competitiveness in the marketplace.
</P>
<P>
The province's Little Swan automatic washing machines have
occupied 40 percent shares of the domestic markets. And the Yaxing
Group's passenger bus and one of Changchai Group's diesel engines
have occupied 25 percent and 26 percent shares of the domestic
market.
</P>
<P>
Local officials predicted that this year, the total sales
volume, taxes and profits, and exports of 16 key enterprises in
the province are expected to increase 20 percent, 15 percent and
30 percent, respectively, all of which exceed the average growth
rates of the industrial enterprises in the province.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen of 21 provincial-level key enterprises in Jiangsu
turned out a combined sales volume of 48.1 billion yuan (about 5.8
billion US dollars) in 1996, up 22.2 percent over the previous
year. Meanwhile, these enterprises' taxes and profits totalled 4.3
billion yuan, up 23.1 percent. The growth rates were 13.6 and 21.5
percentage points higher than the average rates of the province's
industrial enterprises. The sales volume, taxes and profits, and
profits of the 16 enterprises accounted for seven percent, 9.7
percent and 15.8 percent of those of the 40,000 industrial
enterprises in the province.
</P>
<P>
The market shares of the leading products have also expanded
continuously, a local official said. At present, major enterprises
in the province are focusing efforts on key products, accumulating
assets, improving technology, setting up projects in other
countries, and intensifying involvement with multinational
companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
