<HEADLINE> Qingdao Has High-tech Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A high-tech industrial group has
formed in Qingdao, a coastal city in east China's Shandong
Province, since a high-tech industrial park was set up in the city
five years ago.
</P>
<P>
"As many as 28 countries and regions have invested in the
park," said Liu Shiguang, director of the management committee of
the Qingdao High-Tech Industrial Park, adding that the accumulated
foreign contractual investment had reached 1.1 billion US dollars,
with an actual foreign investment of 270 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among the more than 460 enterprises registered in the park,
there are 41 high-tech enterprises, making advanced products such
as the 5ESS-2000 program-controlled switchboard manufactured by
AT&AMP;T, and the air-conditioner and washing machine produced by
Haier using computer-controlled technologies. 
</P>
