<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Attractive to Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Jiangxi Province's efforts to
improve its investment environment in recent years have begun to
pay off, with exports of 1,268 overseas-backed enterprises up 21
percent in the first quarter from the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Last year, their exports were worth 250 million US dollars, up
36 percent from the year before.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, Jiangxi has paid greater attention to
infrastructure, completing 160 key projects in recent years,
increasing its power capacity by 2.3 million kilowatts, adding
3,500 km of highways, and expanding telephone switchboards by 1.6
million lines.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of the year, the province implemented a new
plan for infrastructure facilities involving investment of more
than 10 billion yuan (about 1.2 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
At a recent trade fair in Shenzhen, the province showed its
appeal to overseas investors. Businessmen from 17 countries or
regions have been optimistic about the province's abundant natural
resources and geographical advantages and signed agreements on 163
projects involving 428 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The province's exports continue to increase, and by the end of
March, exports were worth 330.6 million US dollars, up 7.3 percent
from the same period of last year. The province plans to have 1.65
billion US dollars worth of exports by the end of this year, said
Bi Bisheng, director of provincial Foreign Trade and Economic
Co-operation Department.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Jiangxi got 470 million US dollars worth of overseas
investment, 301 million of which was direct investment. But the
official hopes that this year 450 million US dollars will come.
</P>
<P>
The province has approved 3,478 overseas-backed projects, with
contractual investment of more than 3.46 billion US dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
