<HEADLINE> 4 Filipinos Killed in Grenade Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Three brothers and their sisters,
all minors, were killed Monday when a grenade they were playing
exploded in a village in the southern Philippines, the Philippine
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the victims lived 11 kilometers south of
Bacolod City, the capital city of Negros Occidental province.
Their parents were working in a sugarcane field when the tragedy
occurred.
</P>
<P>
The mother of the victims was quoted as saying that the grenade
came from the children's uncle, reportedly a member of a vigilante
group.
</P>
<P>
Leopoldo Bataoil, provincial director of the Philippine
National Police, went to the area. He said the explosion was set
off by the elder Rubico, who chopped the grenade with an
instrument possibly out of curiosity. 
</P>
