<HEADLINE> Zambia to Hold First National Micro-Credit Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The first micro-credit open forum
will be held here next week to prepare for the southern African
regional summit scheduled for August.
</P>
<P>
The forum is meant to bring together various stakeholders to
develop the micro-credit infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
"The national open forum intends to identify some major
players in micro-credit, with whom they coordinate and from whom
they obtain assistance, what role they play in the scenario and
what future prospects there are for the micro-credit as a
service and the beneficiaries," said Natasha Banda, public
relations manager of the Opportunity Center.
</P>
<P>
The forum and the regional summit are follow-ups to the
Washington micro-credit summit held in February this year.
</P>
<P>
It was observed during the Washington meeting that Africa
would fully participate in the global movement to eradicate
poverty through micro-credit and related financial services by
the year 2005. 
