<HEADLINE> Shanghai Working out Strategy for Next Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China's largest metropolis is busy
working on its agenda for the 21st century, a 'White Paper' on
population, the environment and development for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The work began in January of this year and will be completed in
about a year, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The "21st Century Agenda China -- Shanghai Program" is intended
to incorporate the national program and the city's long-term
development blueprint for the period up to 2010.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Program is a general strategy for sustained
development in the city in the next century, touching on all
aspects of the economy, social development, infrastructure,
resources, and environmental protection, officials say.
</P>
<P>
They say that the city government has also selected several
areas that may affect co-ordinative development in the city and
which merit priority. One or two districts or counties will be
made pilot areas for comprehensive social development experiments,
according to the officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
