<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Aids Educational Charity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Construction Bank of China (CBC)
Tibetan branch recently contributed 50,000 yuan to help drop-outs
return to the classroom.
</P>
<P>
The move, jointly launched by the Communist Youth League, the
CBC Tibetan branch, and the Tibetan Youth Development Foundation,
is part of "Project Hope," China's biggest educational charity.
</P>
<P>
Some Tibetan celebrities have also donated money.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that since 1992, the region has received a total
of more than 40 million yuan to provide financial support for more
than 10,000 children in local poverty-stricken
areas. Additionally, 108 new primary schools have been set up, and
20 rebuilt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
