<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Volunteers Create a Better Neighborhood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- About 720,000 volunteers in
Shanghai do their part to help residents in their neighborhoods.
</P>
<P>
This has improved relations among neighbors in the blocks where
they live, local residents said.
</P>
<P>
Ji Wantao, a 74-year-old retired worker, often voluntarily
repairs shoes for his neighbors.
</P>
<P>
"I repaired five pairs of shoes today," the old man said
proudly, when being interviewed by Xinhua reporters.
</P>
<P>
The number of volunteers has steadily been increasing,
according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that Shanghai has about 2,417 teams of
volunteers, with a total of 720,000 team members, including
government officials, workers, and students.
</P>
<P>
"It is really exciting to see so many volunteers in our city,
and they are creating a 'happy big family' for us to live in,"
said Zhou Jinwei, an expert in the Shanghai Institute of Social
Sciences.
</P>
<P>
City dwellers used to have their doors shut all day to their
neighbors, often not even knowing the name of those who lived on
the same floor of their building for decades.
</P>
<P>
But changes have taken place, as volunteers bring harmony into
the community they live in, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
When Xu Yizhong and Chen Yong, a couple of retired teachers in
the No. 860 Building of Qinzhou Street, started clearing away the
dirty spots on the surface of their building, most of their
neighbors thought the couple were workers from housing
administration departments.
</P>
<P>
All their neighbors immediately joined them to clean the
building, when they found out that the couple were their neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Community volunteers provide services for their neighbors such
as repair of electrical appliances, medical care, art design, and
helping students with their lessons, etc.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said that residents in nearly 30,000 buildings
do not even have to walk out of their buildings if they want minor
help. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
