<HEADLINE> Inflation Rises in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's inflation rate has risen
from 10 percent in April to 11.8 percent in May this year,
reported the local daily the New Vision today.
</P>
<P>
This was the highest inflation figure registered since the
beginning of this year, according to Commissioner for Statistics
E. Muwanga-Zake.
</P>
<P>
He said increases were observed in food, household goods, as
well as transport and communication items.
</P>
<P>
There was a steady increase in inflation starting from April
to May this year, a situation that the commissioner said should
be blamed on sharp increases in the prices of foodstuff.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains in May also made roads to most food outlets
impassable, resulting in higher transport charges for food items,
he noted. 
</P>
