<HEADLINE> Fujian Sees Good Performance of Joint-Stock Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Joint-stock companies in China's
coastal Fujian Province have reported good economic performance,
official figures show.
</P>
<P>
The figures show that share-holding companies in Fujian post an
average profit-to-sales rate of 5.9 percent and a net-asset yield
rate of 10.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Fujian introduced share-issuing enterprises in 1984. To date,
the province has set up 2,220 limited-liabilities companies and 86
joint-stock limited companies, with a combined capital stock of
7.23 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The effort to turn enterprises into joint-stock companies has
laid a foundation for the establishment of a modern corporate
system and helped open a new channel to raise funds, analysts say.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Fujian's joint-stock companies have raised
six billion yuan in the aggregate, more than 70 percent of which
is used for technical renovation and development of new products.
</P>
<P>
Joint-stock transformation has also increased the net asset
value of enterprises by an average of 30 percent, statistics
show.  
</P>
</TEXT>
