<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition to Participate in Manikganj </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dhaka, June 3 (Xinhua) -- the main opposition Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP) will take part in the June 30 by-election
in Manikganj-3 constituency "for the sake of democracy and
following the assurance by the Election Commission," BNP sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The BNP had earlier announced that it would not contest any
by-election under the present Chief Election Commissioner Abu
Hena, blaming the latter for his alleged partisan role in the
elections.
</P>
<P>
The Manikganj-3 seat was vacated after the death of the BNP
lawmaker Alhaj Nizamuddin Khan in March this year.
</P>
<P>
Following mounting pressure from within the party to contest
the polls in the BNP's traditional stronghold, the BNP's Standing
Committee gave this decision at a meeting on Monday night,
according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The meeting noted that the Election Commission has given a
positive reply to the BNP's 10-point demand, set by the party as a
precondition to join the by-election. The commission has
reportedly accepted all the suggestions of the BNP except the
demand for the removal of the chief election commissioner.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ruling Awami League has also invited
applications from intending candidates for contesting the
Manikganj-3 constituency by-elections, a party press release said.
</P>
<P>
