<HEADLINE> Japan Slams S.Korea's Plans for Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Japan expressed regret Monday over
South Korea's plan to develop the disputed islands in the Sea of
Japan.
</P>
<P>
Ryozo Kato, director general of the Japanese Foreign Ministry's
Asian Affairs Bureau, summoned South Korean Minister to Japan, Kim
Yong Kyoo, to express regret over South Korea's ongoing
construction of a wharf on the island chain, a press report quoted
ministry officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
The islands, claimed by both Tokyo and Seoul, are known as
Takeshima in Japan and Tokto in South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Kato asked Kim for a halt in construction of the wharf and
cancellation of a development plan announced in South Korea late
last week.
</P>
<P>
South Korea said last Friday it would build berth facilities
and lighthouses, conduct surveys and establish a maritime and
scientific base on the islands.\
</P>
<P>
While reiterating Seoul's stance that the islands belong to
South Korea, Kim was quoted as telling Kato that he will convey
the message to the Seoul government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
