<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Trade Union Plays Big Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Metallurgical
Holdings Company and the Shanghai Metallurgical Workers' Union
recently reached agreement on democratic participation of business
operations by the employees and protection of their rights.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed after negotiations between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
Local observers say that the enterprise-trade union negotiation
system is a significant aspect of the democratic status of the
employees.
</P>
<P>
According to reliable sources, the city's metallurgical sector
has faced hard times this year and the enterprise-employee
relationship needed to be stablized, readjusted, and coordinated.
</P>
<P>
The president of the firm and the trade union chairman took
part in the talks on behalf of the respective sides. They came to
the conclusion that workers must be made well-informed about the
major issues of the industry, including mergers and bankruptcy,
and employees must participate in decision-making on important
matters.
</P>
<P>
As the ongoing industrial restructuring has laid off more
employees, the two sides agreed to protect the rights of layoffs,
to help them find new jobs, and to set up more funds to finance
these laborers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
