<HEADLINE> Five Women to Join Gujral's Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister I. K. Gujral is
expected to expand his council of ministers today by inducting
five women ministers into it in a bid to reaffirm his commitment
to giving adequate representation to women in government, an
informed source said here today.
</P>
<P>
At the moment, there is only one woman minister in the
40-member cabinet -- Minister of State for Coal Kanti Singh.
</P>
<P>
Gujral's plan to induct women members into his cabinet is in
keeping with his commitment soon after his cabinet was sworn in on
April 21 this year. His move is also seen as an attempt to placate
women members who have been resentful of the concerted bid to
block passage of the women's bill in the parliament to reserve
one-third of seats in the parliament and state assemblies for
women. Last year the United Front government tabled the women's
bill before the parliament, yet it has not been passed due to
strong opposition by various parties and men MPs.
</P>
<P>
Today's cabinet expansion will be the first one by Gujral after
he assumed office as the prime minister on April 21.  
</P>
