<HEADLINE> Thai Diamond Exports Predicted Higher This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is expected to export 23
billion baht (920 million U.S. dollars) worth of diamonds this
year, an increase of 13.7 percent over last year, a leading Thai
research institute predicted.
</P>
<P>
The diamond exports will account for 40 percent of Thailand's
total jewelry exports this year, still remaining highest in the
sector, according to the Thai Farmers Research Center.
</P>
<P>
Thai jewelry exports ranked fifth among the country's largest
export earners last year after computers and parts, garments,
rubber, and electric circuit boards, the center said in a report
released recently.
</P>
<P>
The center also pointed out that the Thai diamond industry is
facing problems like shortages of raw materials and high labor
cost.
</P>
<P>
It urged the government and the private sector to join hands to
ease these problems.  
</P>
