<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Seize Food Items From Rebel Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Advancing Sri Lankan Troops seized
large quantities of hoarded food items from a Tamil rebel camp
located in the Nedunkeni area in the Northern province, according
to military sources today.
</P>
<P>
The food was meant for civilians in the North but the rebels
had captured them.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the advancing troops in the heart of rebel
territory overran the rebel camp where the looted food items were
found in the past days.
</P>
<P>
The items included 77,000 kilograms of rice, 55,000 kilograms
of sugar, 22,500 kilograms of dhal, 88,000 kilograms of wheat
flour and 6,300 kilograms of dried chillies.
</P>
<P>
The food was originally distributed by the government to local
families, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the troops were consolidating themselves and
preparing to further advance into rebel territory.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 14-year guerrilla war
against the government for a separate state in the north and east
of the country.  
</P>
