<HEADLINE> Lukasenko Praises Belarusian-Sino Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Belarusian President Alexandr
Lukasenko today spoke highly of the efforts by Chinese leaders to
develop friendly and cooperative relations between Belarus and
China.
</P>
<P>
Belarus would, as always, seek to enhance its friendly
cooperative ties with China and the ties enjoyed bright prospects
and a great potential, Lukasenko said. He was meeting visiting
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian in Minsk, the capital of
Belarus.
</P>
<P>
The president said Chi's visit showed progress in the two
countries' military links, and was an important step towards
further boosting the friendly and cooperative relationship between
Belarus and China.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Chi, also the vice-chairman of the Central
Military Commission of China and state councillor, conveyed
President Jiang Zemin's cordial regards and good wishes to
Lukasenko. He thanked Lukasenko for Belarusian support for China
over the issues of Taiwan, Tibet and human rights.
</P>
<P>
China and Belarus have an old friendship and Sino-Belarusian
ties have been constantly developed in politics, trade and
economy, science and technology and military affairs since
Belarus' independence, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Belarusian people were heroes who made great
sacrifices in the war against the German Fascists in World War
II. The Chinese people wished the Belarusian people and troops,
under the leadership of President Lukasenko, would make new
achievements in the sacred cause of constructing and defending
their motherland, said the Chinese defense minister.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who arrived in Minsk Sunday for an official visit, met his
Belarus' counterpart Alexandr Chumakov early today. 
</P>
