<HEADLINE> More Distribution Centers Built for Chain-stores in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is building more
commodity distribution centers to support the fast-growing
chain-store business.
</P>
<P>
As chain stores spring-up along the Shanghai-Nanjing and
Shanghai-Hangzhou expressways, local commerce conglomerates such
as Hualian and Lianhua plan to build distribution centers in the
Yangtze River Delta areas, with several devoted to special
commodities.
</P>
<P>
The commerce sector of Shanghai last year invested a total of
3.45 billion yuan (415.66 million US dollars) in the building of
shopping facilities totalling in 816,800 sq.m.
</P>
<P>
Among the projects, 45.8 percent were located in neighboring
areas in the Yangtze River Delta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
