<HEADLINE> Chinese Kindergarten Employs Young Brit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A 29-year-old British man has
found work for nearly a year in a kindergarten in Anshan City in
Liaoning Province in northeast China, going against the
traditional trend in the country.
</P>
<P>
Mark Turner, who got a bachelor's degree in education in
Britain in 1994, was hired by the Anshan City Art Kindergarten in
August of last year.
</P>
<P>
He says that he chose to work in a Chinese kindergarten because
Chinese kindergartens suffer from a serious lack of male teachers
and that he likes children's education very much.
</P>
<P>
He teaches English, simple craftsmanship, painting, and
gymnastics. At the same time, he studies Chinese martial arts,
massage techniquesm and acupuncture in his spare time. 
