<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Develops Fishing Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Heilongjiang Province in
northeast China has reinforced its fishing industry to make it an
important part of its rural economy.
</P>
<P>
With a water-covered area of 654,000 ha, the province has
bountiful resources to develop the fishing industry, but most of
the area has yet to be developed.
</P>
<P>
The province has taken measures to further utilize the
resources. It has auctioned the use-rights of small ponds,
reservoirs and fishing farms to individuals. Share-holding systems
have been adopted in the management of large fishing farms, with
50-year leases available.
</P>
<P>
The role of science and technology is emphasized. New
techniques have been adopted and the production level has been
improved.
</P>
<P>
The province has also encouraged more farmers to enter into the
market directly and has set up an information network on aquatic
products. 
</P>
