<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Sets National Record in Using Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, a port city in north
China, exceeded all the other Chinese cities in the use of
overseas investment in the first four months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Between January to April, the city approved 290 foreign-funded
enterprises, involving contractual agreements worth 1.6 billion US
dollars, said Vice Mayor Ye Disheng.
</P>
<P>
Investment from Hong Kong and Taiwan increased by 70 percent
compared to the same period of last year to reach 400 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment flowing into Tianjin in the first four
months was 80 percent higher over last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
The vice mayor attributed the growth to good investment
climate, such as sufficient supply of experienced workers,
complete infrastructure and its strategic marketing positions
in northern part of China.
</P>
<P>
To date, more than 10,000 foreign-funded enterprises have been
built in Tianjin, absorbing 17 billion US dollars, and two third
of them fall into the manufacturing industry. About 190 of the top
500 companies in the world have set footholds in the city. More
than 400,000 Chinese are working the in foreign-funded firms.
</P>
</TEXT>
