<HEADLINE> China to Allow More Materials Firms to Conduct Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China will allow more commercial
and industrial materials enterprises to conduct foreign trade,
according to a report.
</P>
<P>
After a three-year trial period, the qualifications imposed on
206 enterprises, as required of commercial firms applying for
foreign-trade rights, were formally recognized in a recent
government document.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises in the category applying for foreign-trade rights
must have fixed assets worth more than 10 million yuan (about 1.2
million US dollars), China Daily said today.
</P>
<P>
The document was jointly issued by the State Economic and Trade
Commission, the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
and the Ministry of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
The regulations required that coastal enterprises in this
category must show sales of at least one billion yuan (121 million
US dollars) compared with at least 300 million yuan required of
such enterprises in inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Industrial materials and commercial retail enterprises that
mainly buy and sell machinery and electronic products in coastal
areas must sell more than 600 million yuan worth of products and
those in inland areas more than 200 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Retail enterprises' annual sales must exceed 300 million yuan,
according to the document. 
</P>
</TEXT>
