<HEADLINE> Video Game "Opium War" to Go on Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The video game of "Opium War" will
hit Chinese and overseas markets in mid-June to celebrate Hong
Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
China's first video game that depicts an anti-invasion event in
modern times was developed by the Optical Memory National
Engineering Research Center of Qinghua University. "Opium War" is
aimed at teaching players about China's humiliating history of the
Opium War and inspiring patriotic spirit among Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Through playing, people can gain a better understanding of Lin
Zexu, whose ban of Britain's notorious opium trade with China
touched off the historic Opium War between China and Britain from
1840 to 1842.
</P>
<P>
They will also become familiar with other anti-British generals
such as Deng Tingzhen and Guan Tianpei in the war, which resulted
the ceding of Hong Kong to Britain.
</P>
<P>
After experimenting with the game, teachers and students at
Beijing Fourth Secondary School said that it is "interesting and
instructive." 
</P>
