<HEADLINE> Thai Consumer Price Index for May Rose 4.3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK June 3 (Xinhua) -- Thai consumer price index (CPI) for
May rose 4.3 percent year-on-year, the same increase recorded
previous month, according to the Business Economic Department of
the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The monthly index was up 0.4 percent from April. That increase
was attributed to a jump of 0.7 percent in the price of goods
under the non-food sector. In particular the price of clothing was
up 1.2 and the cost of educational necessities up 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The overall price of food fell 0.1 percent, with the cost of
fresh fruits and vegetables dropping 3.9 percent. However, the
price of rice and rice products was up 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The inflation over the entire year is forecast to come in below
5 percent. 
</P>
