<HEADLINE> Chinese Strongwoman Lifts World Record to Win Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAPETOWN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese strongwoman Ding Meiyuan
set a snatch world record en route to winning the over 83kg
category at the World Youth Weightlifting Championships here on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ding Meiyuan, a debutant in international competitions, lifted
109 kilograms to better the previous mark of 108.5, which was set
by her countrywoman Wang Yannei in Warsaw in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old lifter jerked 132.5 kilograms for a winning
total of 240 kilograms to take the crown.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Chia-I from Chinese Taipei was second at 220, with 95
from the snatch and 125 from the jerk.
</P>
<P>
Baker Olivia of New Zealand, who snatched 82.5 and jerked 112,
had the bronze medal at 197.5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
