<DOCNO> XIE19970603.0270 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Province to Shake Off Poverty This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Poor farmers in northeast China's
Liaoning Province will leave poverty behind by the end of this
year, as the provincial government pledges to wind up the
anti-poverty campaign as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to help farmers in its remaining five poor
counties lead a life with adequate food and clothing, by ensuring
every village has convenient transportation, electricity, and
clean drinking water.
</P>
<P>
More than two million poor farmers in 11 counties have been
freed from poverty over the past decade thanks to concerted
efforts from people in all walks of life, said a provincial
official.
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 officials were grouped into poverty relief
working teams, and they managed to have over one billion yuan
invested in the poor areas, involving more than 2,000 projects.
</P>
<P>
The officials helped farmers develop forest industry, raise
cattle, and grow greenhouse vegetables. As a result, the poor
farmers have greatly improved their life, with 594 kg of grain and
1390 yuan of income per capita. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
