<HEADLINE> Uzbekstan Expects Good Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Favorable weather has enabled
Uzbekstan a better grain harvest than in previous years, according
to reports from the Uzbek capital of Tashkent.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that total grain output this year will reach 4
million tons as compared to 3.35 million tons last year.
</P>
<P>
Uzbekstan, a country with a population of 2.3 million, needs
3.8 to 4 million tons of grain a year to meet the consumption
demand. Uzbekstan has been trying hard to meet the goal.
</P>
<P>
At present, harvesting has begun in the southern
grain-producing regions, with 200 more combines being mobilized
for the season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
