<HEADLINE> Australian Beats Netherlands in Champions Trophy Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Australia defeated the Netherlands
2-0 at the women's Champions Trophy here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The win put them ahead on goal difference on the United States
in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Alyson Annan and Jennifer Morris scored the goals that
confirmed the title holders' dominance but Dutch coach Tom van't
Hek expressed his pleasure with his young side whilst paying
tribute to the Australians.
</P>
<P>
Germany, with goals from Inga Moller and local Berlin heroine
Natascha Keller, were leading 2-0 four minutes into the second
half against the United States, who caused much surprise on the
opening day with a 1-0 win against South Korea, only to be pegged
back to 2-2.
</P>
<P>
Tara Maguire and Kelli James finished off sweeping moves by the
Americans to share the points.
</P>
<P>
Olympic silver medallists South Korea collected their first
points with a 2-0 win against Great Britain but left it to the
last 10 minutes before opening he scoring through Eun Kyung
Choi. With just two minutes remaining, as Britain pressed for the
equaliser, Ji Young Lee, on the break, collected the second.
