<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fredericks Wins 100 Meters at Athletics Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Namibian Frankie Fredericks defeated
younger sprint rival Ato Boldon to win the 100 meters at the Grand
Prix II meeting at St. Denis on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Fredericks, the Olympic 100 and 200m silver medallist, clocked
10.09 seconds on a damp track as Trinidadian Boldon, third in the
short sprint in Atlanta, faded badly to finish fourth in 10.23,
compared with his season's fastest of 9.89.
</P>
<P>
The usually fast St. Denis track was made sluggish by
intermittent rain during the early evening and Fredericks was
never likely to threaten his season's best of 9.90.
</P>
<P>
Indeed it was Boldon who broke fastest at the gun and he led
clearly at 50m before being swallowed up as Fredericks used his
200m strength to roar through the centre ahead of American Brian
Lewis (10.19) and Davidson Ezinwa of Nigeria (10.20).
</P>
<P>
Other highlights of Monday's programme included an
authoritative performance by Moroccan Hicham El Guerrouj, who
clocked 3:31.76 in the 1,500m.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Jamaican Merlene Ottey won the women's 100m in 11.19,
pipping Nigerian Chioma Ajunwa by 1/100th of a second.
</P>
<P>
There was disappointment for Britain's Colin Jackson, who
finished a lowly fifth in the 110m hurdles in 13.57. American Mark
Crear won the race in 13.29.
</P>
<P>
France's Olympic champion Jean Galfione also fared badly,
surprisingly failing to clear 5.60m in the pole vault. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
