<P>
CANBERRA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Australian
</P>
<P>
-- A scheme that delays by five years the federal government's
plans to cut car tariffs to 15 percent from 2000 to 2005 will
prompt a showdown between the government's top economic ministers.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald
</P>
<P>
-- The federal treasury has directly contradicted government
claims about its 15 percent savings rebate, the centerpiece of
last month's budget, saying it may backfire and lead to lower
national savings.
</P>
<P>
The Age
</P>
<P>
-- Melbourne researchers have discovered the missing ingredient
that could enable scientists to build artificial chromosomes to
treat haemophilia and cystic fibrosis.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- US giant Chevron Oil Corp. is set to unveil a
multi-billion-dollar proposal to develop the massive Gorgon gas
field off the coast of Western Australia.  
