<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Parliament Speaker Meets Chinese Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Greek Parliament Speaker Apostolos
Kaklamanis and visiting Chinese leader Li Ruihuan today expressed
their hope that bilateral ties between the two countries should be
further developed and such ties conform to the fundamental
interests of both sides.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting here this evening, Kaklamanis stressed
that all political parties in Greece are in favor of boosting ties
with China.
</P>
<P>
The Greek people admire very much the achievements China has
made in recent years, he said, adding that the progress has laid a
solid foundation for furthering Greek-Sino relations.
</P>
<P>
Kaklamanis also expressed his satisfaction with China's
progress in democracy and the political fields.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that democracy has no fixed pattern and should
not be imposed upon others, saying that the form and process of
democracy could only be decided by each country in accordance with
their own realities.
</P>
<P>
In response, Li Ruihuan said that China and Greece, both being
ancient civilized countries, now face the common task of
developing their economies and improving people's living
standards.
</P>
<P>
There exist no conflicts of interests between China and Greece,
he noted, adding that the two countries have common aspirations of
safeguarding world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and Greece have common interests in
developing bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that my current visit will help continue the high-level
contacts between the two countries and further develop friendship
and cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed Kaklamanis on China's development of democracy,
saying that democracy is an objective, a way and also a process.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that the Chinese people's general objective is to
build their country into a rich, democratical and civilized
country.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that China and Greece should strengthen
exchange and dialogue and make contributions to modern democracy.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived in Greece from Portugal for a five-day goodwill
visit to Greece, the second leg of his three-nation European trip,
which will also take him to Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
